headline: Hormel Foods (NYSE:HRL) Beats Q4 Sales Targets
summary: Packaged foods company Hormel (NYSE:HRL) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q4 CY2024, but sales were flat year on year at $2.99 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $12.05 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.35 per share was 8% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Hormel Foods misses quarterly profit estimates on higher input costs
summary: Hormel Foods, which sells snacking and packaged meat products, has also taken a hit due to lower whole turkey prices and increased advertising expenses.  Meanwhile, demand for certain packaged products suffered as the company kept the prices elevated to protect its margins from inflated input costs.  Hormel's Planters nut brand faced a supply disruption at its Suffolk, Virginia-based distribution facility due to an unspecified food safety issue last April, which continued to impact the company's margins in the first quarter.
